modules.description: Provides functions to inspect and extract the internal representations of abstract types from the Unix module, such as file descriptors and time values. Works with types like `Unix.file_descr`, `Unix.time_val`, and `Unix.time_spec`. Enables low-level interaction with Unix system calls and time management functions.

Converts Unix file descriptors and directory handles to and from native integers, enabling low-level system interaction. Works with Unix.file_descr and Unix.dir_handle types, as well as nativeint and int. Used to interface with C libraries or system calls requiring raw file descriptor or directory pointer values.
